        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 2:48PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 247 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mt Pleasant, or 7 miles southeast of Downtown Concord, moving
northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Albemarle, Plyler, Fairview In Union County, Locust, Norwood,
Oakboro, Stanfield, Richfield, New London, and Finger.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
